directory: crates/ctx-summarize/tests
domain: Integration test suite for the ctx-summarize crate's runner, verifying end-to-end summarization ordering, safety gating (path/scope/prompt/secret checks), and the Fs/Agent trait contracts against both fake and real (subprocess) implementations.
edit_notes:
  - Single file (summarize.rs); when ctx_summarize::fs::Fs or ctx_summarize::agent::Agent trait signatures change, FakeFs and RecordingAgent test doubles here must be updated in lockstep.
  - Subprocess-based tests require `sh` on PATH; no network access needed or used.
children:
  - summarize.rs: Full integration test suite — runner ordering, error gating, Fs/Agent contract checks.
invariants:
  - runner::run never writes or modifies intent.md, only .ctx files, and always writes leaves before rollups in leaf-to-root order.
  - Path traversal (".."), missing prompts, oversized unapproved scope, and secret-like target paths are all rejected with distinct SummError variants.